## Common Pitfalls to Avoid
- **Random train/test split on time-series**: Always use TimeSeriesSplit — random split leaks future data into training
- **Training on labeled flat candles**: Class imbalance (lots of FLAT labels) will bias the model — undersample FLAT or use class weights
- **Feature look-ahead**: Every feature must only use data available at prediction time — check each one carefully
- **Deploying without validation**: Never swap to a new model without comparing against holdout performance
- **Over-engineering early**: Start with RAG + XGBoost. Add complexity only when simpler approach fails.

